<dd class='comment-body'>
<p>In fact, DBAN is a Linux boot disc. I doubt that any normal recovery tool will be able to find a scrap of anything on a hard drive that's been thoroughly DBAN'ed. If you're that paranoid, you should physically shred the drive into little bits (there are machines which do this) and just to be sure, melt the bits in a furnace.</p>
</dd>
