<dd class='comment-body'>
<p>100 passes? That sounds like a bit too much. I seem to recall that your average hard disk can take like 20 passes before the drive starts to degrade. <BR/><BR/>Anyways. For those who don't have shred installed (some unixes for example), it is easy to replicate the effects.<BR/><BR/>dd if=/dev/urandom of=/dev/hda bs=4096<BR/>(block size will vary, depending on file system)<BR/>repeat this a dozen or so times.</p>
</dd>
