<dt class='comment-author ' id='c377482792101005347'>
<a name='c377482792101005347'></a>
mindgame
said...
</dt>
<dd class='comment-body'>
<p># shred -vfz -n 100 /dev/hda <BR/><BR/>This command only write zero in the final pass. The first 99 passes are written with random data.<BR/><BR/>100 passes may significantly shorten the life of you harddisk, if not break it during the process. You drive temperature may rise to 50+ Celsius, where the thermal stress may cause physical damage to the harddisk hardware.</p>
</dd>
<dd class='comment-footer'>
<span class='comment-timestamp'>
<a href='http://linuxhelp.blogspot.com/2006/06/how-to-securely-erase-hard-disk-before.html?showComment=1192934820000#c377482792101005347' title='comment permalink'>
